        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:09AM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 409 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Benton, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Benton, Ducktown, William L. Davenport Refuge, Coker Creek, Violet,
Parksville, Turtletown, Hiawasse Dam, Reliance, and Archville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
